<section style="background: #0F172A; padding: 4rem 2rem;">
  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; color: #F8FAFC;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: #F8FAFC;">AI Amplifies, It Doesn't Replace</h2>

    <p style="color: #CBD5E1; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      There's a narrative out there that AI is coming to take jobs, replace creativity, and make humans obsolete.
    </p>

    <p style="color: #CBD5E1; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      That's not how I see it.
    </p>

    <p style="color: #CBD5E1; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      AI is a lever. It's an amplifier. It takes what you already know and makes it faster, sharper, more scalable.
      But without human judgment, human creativity, and human empathy, AI is just noise.
    </p>

    <p style="color: #CBD5E1; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      I use AI to generate drafts, not finished products. To suggest ideas, not dictate them.
      To speed up the boring parts so I can focus on the parts that matter — the strategy, the story, the soul.
    </p>

    <p style="color: #CBD5E1; line-height: 1.8;">
      That's the philosophy behind TCTC Business Suite: <strong style="color: #F8FAFC;">AI amplifies human creativity, it doesn't replace it.</strong>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

